How we use it
-------------
- Thariq's original HTML gallery is included **only** as a pinned git submodule
  at `upstream/html-effectiveness/`. It is never modified in place; it stays
  verbatim and remains clearly his work, attributable through its own git
  history. Clone with `--recurse-submodules` to fetch it.
- The artifact *design system* in this repo (color palette, typography, layout
  conventions, and the "single self-contained HTML document" approach) takes
  aesthetic inspiration from that gallery, but our implementation
  (`obsidian-plugin/src/artifacts/designSystem.ts` and the `claude-plugin`
  note-to-artifact skill) is an **original reformulation** — it expresses a
  similar sensibility in our own prompt and code, and is NOT a copy of the
  original HTML files.
- Project-specific variations live in
  `claude-plugin/design-system/extensions/` as additive layers, so the original
  set is never altered.

If you are Thariq and would like attribution changed or removed, please open an
issue on the repository.

